            "id": "c33bf8d19bdb4bdba0645",
            "questionText": "A biomedical researcher uses a micrometer screw gauge to measure the diameter of a microscopic fiber. The instrument has a positive zero error of $!$0.02\\,mm$!$ and gives an uncorrected reading of $!$1.28\\,mm$!$. The instrument measures to $!$0.01\\,mm$!$. Calculate the actual diameter of the fiber in metres, expressing your answer in standard notation with the appropriate number of significant figures.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "3f496a0f36e948e79be14",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining how to adjust the uncorrected reading for the positive zero error. Identify the correct operation needed to obtain the corrected measurement.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "9a4da118-2c7f-416d-9990-5c7e8ca6e378"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Corrected reading} = \\text{Uncorrected reading} - \\text{Zero error}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Corrected reading} = \\text{Uncorrected reading} + \\text{Zero error}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Corrected reading} = \\text{Uncorrected reading}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "97dd8003a90f40f5a3af0",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now that you know to subtract the zero error, perform the numerical calculation to obtain the corrected diameter in millimetres. Then, convert this value from millimetres to metres using the fact that $!$1\\,mm=10^{-3}\\,m$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1.26e-3"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "97df9a78-627f-40ae-8aef-c68ba9dd9ec7"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "db43788e6e46469694e27",
                    "stepText": "Finally, express your answer in standard notation with the appropriate number of significant figures. Select the option that correctly represents the final answer.",
